text:
- My name is Ceren, I'm a
startup solutions architect,
based in London.
(lighthearted music)

In my day-to-day job, I help
customers to get started
and grow on AWS.

Working with startups, being
in the startup ecosystem
is the most exciting part of my job.

I'm able to see what's
coming next, the future
of technology, so it's quite exciting.

I joined AWS a year and a
half ago with Tech U Program.

Tech U is a new graduate program
for early career talents.

It's a great way to start your
career in AWS because I think

it's such a comprehensive
program to develop skills.

Apart from my role, I'm
also a volunteer for
the AWS re/Start Program.

Re/Start is a program to train
underemployed communities
and people.

And when I volunteer
there I actually make,

conduct mock interviews with
attendants so that they can

actually upskill themselves
to be better interviewers.

Sustainability is my passion
and I try to enable people
and customers about how they can be better
at sustainability, how they can optimize
their infrastructures.
(lighthearted music)

If I were to describe my
experience in AWS in three words

I would say dynamic,
diverse, and exciting.
(lighthearted music)
